				<div class="box">
			<h3>Editorial comment</h3>
			<p>The EU Agriculture Council recommendation of 19 October to allocate an additional €280 million in response to the dairy crisis brings the additional budgetary assistance allocated to the EU dairy sector to €880 million. However, despite modifying how a range of instruments is to be deployed, the EC has nevertheless maintained the overall trajectory of CAP reform, in terms of the eventual abolition of production quotas in 2015. The impact these measures will have on overall EU production and trade will be determined largely by the state of global dairy markets at this time and the ability of EU dairy companies to make the transition to producing and exporting higher-value dairy products. In any case, by 2015 the traditional pattern of EU dairy exports and its adverse effects on ACP efforts to develop their own dairy sectors is likely to be a thing of the past.</p>
		</div>
		
